by javiereguiluz at 2015-04-15T11:10:36Z

I must confess that I did this on purpose ... but thanks to your pull request I realized that I was wrong.

The font size of the site name automatically adapts to its length. If you use `ACME` you'll see a big and beautiful site name and if you use `ACME Megacorp` you'll see it in small letters. However, if your site name is really long, the font size no longer changes and the overflow text is lost.

I'm going to test this change in my backends and I'll merge it ASAP. Thanks.

